  <brief_title>Role of Antibodies Against Glutamate Receptors and Double Stranded DNA in Epilepsy Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hadassah Medical Organization</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hadassah Medical Organization</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators will check the serum of epilepsy patients for antibodies against glutamate
      receptors and double stranded DNA. They will characterise the patients (by the kind of
      epilepsy, autoimmune disease comorbidity, and cognitive profile).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
